article.headline: Weber St. 40, Idaho St. 14
article.story: POCATELLO, Idaho -- C.J. Tuckett rushed for 289 yards and two touchdowns to lead Weber State to a 40-14 victory over Idaho State on Saturday. Tuckett scored on runs of 4 and 19 yards for the Wildcats (2-9, 2-6 Big Sky). Mike Hoke passed for 108 yards and a TD, a 7-yard pass to Jordan Clemente, for Weber State. Rodrick Rumble caught eight passes for 171 yards and two third-quarter touchdowns for Idaho State (1-10, 0-8 Big Sky). Rumble's 81-yard TD catch of a Kevin Yost pass was ISU's longest offensive play since 2007. He also had a 33-yard scoring reception.
